  "prompt": "Why does getting Italian citizenship take so long?",
  "response": "Getting Italian citizenship can be a lengthy process for several reasons:\n\n1. Complex requirements\n- Strict documentation requirements\n- Proving direct ancestral lineage\n- Verifying original documents from Italy\n\n2. Bureaucratic processes\n- Multiple government agencies involved\n- Significant administrative paperwork\n- Slow processing times in Italian government offices\n\n3. Verification procedures\n- Extensive background checks\n- Genealogical research\n- Translation and authentication of documents\n\n4. Specific citizenship pathways\n- Different rules for descent, marriage, residency\n- Each pathway has unique timelines and requirements\n- Some routes can take several years\n\n5. Limited appointment slots\n- Consulates often have restricted availability\n- Long waiting lists for citizenship interviews\n- Backlog of applications\n\n6. Legal complications\n- Potential issues with historical documentation\n- Complex family history tracing\n- Requirements for proving continuous lineage\n\n7. Administrative bottlenecks\n- Limited staffing in government offices\n- COVID-19 pandemic further delayed many processes\n- High volume of citizenship applications\n\nThe entire process can take anywhere from 1-10 years depending on the specific citizenship pathway and individual circumstances.",
